txt.en: Catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae can be found on the hills and high ground deep within the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\n\nYou should disable or destroy the catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae.

Catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae can be found on the hills and high ground deep within the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\n\nYou should disable or destroy the catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae.

Catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae can be found on the hills and high ground deep within the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\n\nYou should destroy the siege-equipment in Dol Dínen.
'You have once again shown your cunning and prowess, [placeholder]. With the loss of their siege-engines, the Orc-host will be weakened, but it is not yet destroyed.'
Hithlim awaits your return at Esteldín.\n\nYou entered Dol Dínen and disabled several of the Orcs' ballistae, catapults, and trebuchets. You should bring news of your success back to Hithlim.
'Do not go too deeply into the Orc-encampment alone, [placeholder], but do your best to disable the Orkish siege-engines you find there.'
You have disabled the siege-craft in Dol Dínen, hindering the Ongbúrz march to war. The Rangers of Esteldín will be grateful for your endeavours.
Deliver the siege-engine parts to Hithlim
